data.title: aim Systems aims to transition to an AI Factory, unveiling a new roadmap and demo at AW2026. Production includes AI deployment guide and product demonstrations.
data.description: aim Systems, a South Korea-based smart factory solution innovation company, revealed on February 9, 2026, its plan to release a comprehensive AI Factory deployment guide aimed at assisting businesses in effectively implementing practical AI solutions. As part of this initiative, the company will also conduct professional diagnostic services to showcase the real-world application of their new products. This announcement signifies aim Systems' commitment to enhancing operational efficiency and integrating cutting-edge technologies in the industrial sector. The company's move aligns with the growing demand for advanced solutions, with the upcoming guide expected to provide valuable insights for businesses looking to optimize their processes. Overall, aim Systems' proactive approach in offering practical AI solutions reflects the increasing interest and investment in smart factory technologies.

data.title: LingoAce gains WASC accreditation, setting new standards in supplemental education, joining elite institutions.

data.title: Afghan artist Sonita launches "Donate Your Voice" campaign with UNICEF to give voice to silenced Afghan women.
data.description: Singer and activist Sonita Alizadeh has introduced the "Donate Your Voice" campaign to combat the silence faced by women in Afghanistan. This initiative, in collaboration with UNICEF, encourages individuals worldwide to contribute their voices using a TikTok filter. The campaign was launched in Paris on February 27, 2026.

data.title: Metacon received EUR 2.6 million payment from Motor Oil Hellas for a 50 MW electrolysis plant project milestone.
data.description: In a recent development, Metacon, based in Stockholm, announced on Feb. 27, 2026, that they have successfully received a payment of EUR 2.6 million from Motor Oil Hellas. This amount corresponds to approximately SEK 27.7 million based on the current exchange rate. This payment was made in relation to achieving a significant milestone in the project to supply a 50 MW electrolysis plant. The project's progress underscores the partnership between Metacon and Motor Oil Hellas as they work towards the successful delivery of this substantial electrolysing facility.

data.title: Banco Santander Chile filed its 2025 Annual Report on Form 20-F with the SEC. Symbol NYSE: BSAC; SSE: Bsantander.
data.description: Chilean bank Santander Chile has recently disclosed its 2025 Annual Report to the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. This report covers the fiscal year ending on December 31, 2025. The company, traded under the tickers NYSE: BSAC and SSE: Bsantander, officially submitted its Form 20-F for the mentioned period. This filing provides crucial financial information and performance details to regulators and shareholders.
